# Implementation checklist (125.md)

Use this checklist when implementing or reviewing the Sprint 2 chatbot. Tick items as done.

**Focus:** Domain-focused chatbot with advanced RAG + tool calling using Next.js and LangChain.

## Setup

- [x] Node on LTS (if needed)
- [x] pnpm installed; use it for this project
- [x] Next.js app created in current project folder
- [x] Required dependencies installed (OpenAI SDK, Supabase JS, Zod, LangChain packages, `@langchain/anthropic` for optional Claude path; vectors via Supabase pgvector)
- [x] LangChain orchestration for chat pipeline — `src/lib/llm/salonPipeline.ts` (RunnableSequence: rewrite → retrieve → tools → answer)
- [x] OpenAI API key obtained and stored securely (`.env.local` locally, Vercel env in production; never in code)
- [x] Optional Anthropic: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in `.env.example` / Vercel when using `anthropic:*` ids from `src/lib/llm/modelCatalog.ts`

## Domain definition

- [x] Domain/use case selected and documented (clear scope)
- [x] Knowledge sources selected and added to `data/` (hair-salon KB + pricing, policies, booking context)
- [x] Domain-specific system prompt defined — `src/lib/llm/chat.ts` → `buildGroundedInstructions` + grounded input with `<retrieved_context>`, `<tool_results>`, `<user_message>`
- [x] Basic prompt-injection handling — untrusted user text delimited and called out in system rules (`chat.ts`); optional API moderation not wired

## Core requirements (125.md)

### 1) RAG implementation

- [x] Knowledge base ingestion pipeline implemented
- [x] Chunking strategy configured and documented
- [x] Embeddings-based retrieval implemented
- [x] Similarity search working with relevant top-k retrieval
- [x] Query translation/rewriting — `src/lib/rag/queryRewrite.ts`, used in `runSalonPipeline`
- [x] Response includes source context/citations where possible — API returns citations; `ChatView` renders them

### 2) Tool calling

- [x] At least 3 domain-relevant tools — `checkStylistAvailability`, `getServicePrice`, `suggestAppointmentSlots` under `src/lib/tools/`; orchestration `salonToolRound.ts`
- [x] Tool input schemas validated (Zod on each tool module)
- [x] Tool-call errors handled gracefully — safe strings in tool records / `formatToolResultsForPrompt`
- [x] Tool results rendered clearly in the UI — `ChatView` (tool block before reply)

### 3) Domain specialization

- [x] Chatbot behavior is clearly specialized to chosen domain
- [x] Domain-focused knowledge base integrated into responses
- [x] Domain-specific safety/security considerations applied

### 4) Technical implementation

- [x] LangChain integration for model + retrieval workflow — `salonPipeline.ts`, `createSalonChatModel` (OpenAI + optional Anthropic), tool round messages
- [x] API route validation and sanitization implemented
- [x] Proper error handling added (typed, safe responses)
- [x] Privacy-safe request telemetry — `src/lib/logging/chatTelemetry.ts` (counts, latency, token totals + `modelId` on success; no message body)
- [x] Rate limiting added for chat endpoint
- [x] API key management follows secure env-var practices
- [x] Chat model timeout + limited retries — `openaiClient.ts` / `ChatOpenAI` in `createSalonChatModel.ts`; Anthropic via `clientOptions.timeout`

### 5) User interface

- [x] Intuitive chat interface implemented in Next.js (`/` on `chat.nk-studio.org`, shell, composer)
- [x] Sources/citations displayed from backend in `ChatView`
- [x] Tool-call outputs displayed in dedicated UI area in `ChatView`
- [x] Progress/loading indicators while chat request is in flight

